OOS construction: new shelling, wounded

01 Nov 2019, 07:52


On October 31, the armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries violated the ceasefire 15 times. The wounded man was wounded by one member of the Allied Forces, another wounded.

The enemy fired at the positions of the units of the Joint Forces with the prohibited by the Minsk agreements of 82 mm mortars, as well as grenade launchers of various systems, large machine guns, other small arms and BMP weapons, informs the headquarters of the CAB.
In the area of responsibility of the tactical group "East" the enemy made 7 shells:

near Novogrigorovka and Nevelsky - machine-gun anti-tank grenade launchers;
nearby Kamenka - hand-held anti-tank grenade launchers and small arms;
three times in the water district of the Azov region - with armaments BMP-1, small arms and grenade launchers of different systems;
near Lebedinsky - from large-caliber machine guns.




In the area of responsibility of tactical grouping "North" the enemy carried out 8 shelling:

near Svitlodarsk - automatic grenade launchers;
twice near Lugansk - from large-caliber machine guns and machine-gun anti-tank grenade launchers;
near Novolugansk - automatic grenade launchers and small arms;
near the Crimean - from 82 mm mortars, automatic grenade launchers and large machine guns;
nearby the South - with anti-tank and automatic grenade launchers and small arms;
near the Trinity - from large-caliber machine guns;
near Novotoshkivsky - 82 mm mortars.

From the beginning of this day, armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries, in the area of responsibility of the tactical group "North", fired at our positions near Lugansk with RPGs, large machine guns and other small arms.
No casualties were reported during the current day as a result of enemy shelling.
We will remind, in a zone of carrying out of operation of the Joint forces in Donbass the mode «yellow» is declared. Residence and relocation of Ukrainian citizens in the area of CAB is carried out in the presence of documents.
The police also named the number of volunteers in Gold.
